<li id="cite_note-Tullidge-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Tullidge_17-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Tullidge_17-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFTullidge1877">Tullidge 1877</a>, p.&#160;177</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Hartley-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Hartley_18-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFHartley2001">Hartley 2001</a>, pp.&#160;6, 20–23</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-LeSueur225-19"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-LeSueur225_19-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-LeSueur225_19-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFLeSueur1987">LeSueur 1987</a>, pp.&#160;225, 229, 237–238</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">This refers to an agreement between the Church members leaders and General Samuel Lucas, signed under duress, which compelled the Latter-day Saints to give up their leaders, their arms and all of their lands and property, and to then leave Missouri.  <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://yavanika.org/classes/data/uploads/clarkspeech.pdf">General Clark's Speech</a>, p. 1.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Lin-21"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Lin_21-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Lin_21-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFLin1987">Lin 1987</a><span class="error harv-error" style="display: none; font-size:100%"> harvnb error: no target: CITEREFLin1987 (<a href="/wiki/Category:Harv_and_Sfn_template_errors" title="Category:Harv and Sfn template errors">help</a>)</span></span>
</li>
